{"title_page": "Hard Quiz", "text_new": "{{short description|Australian game quiz show}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox television\n | show_name = Hard Quiz\n | image = Hard_Quiz_ABC_Logo.png\n | image_size = \n | creator = \n | presenter = [[Tom Gleeson]]\n | starring = \n | judges = \n | opentheme = \n | country = Australia\n | language = English\n | num_series = 5\n | num_episodes = 82 <small>(as of 15 April 2020)</small>\n | executive_producer =\n | location =\n | runtime = 30 mins\n | company = \n | network = [[Australian Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n | picture_format = \n | audio_format = \n | first_aired = {{Startdate|2016|10|19|df=y}}\n | last_aired = present\n | related = ''[[The Weekly with Charlie Pickering]]''<br>''[[The Einstein Factor]]''\n | website = http://www.abc.net.au/tv/programs/hard-quiz/\n}}\n'''''Hard Quiz''''' is an Australian television comedy [[quiz show]], which premiered on [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]] on 19 October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|first=David|last=Knox|title=Hard Quiz|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/10/hard-quiz-2.html|website=TV Tonight|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=David|last=Knox|title=Hard Quiz Review|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/10/hard-quiz.html|website=TV Tonight|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref> Hosted by [[Tom Gleeson]], the show is a spin-off of his \"Hard Chat\" segment on the satirical television news program ''[[The Weekly with Charlie Pickering]]''.\n\nGleeson has claimed he was surprised by the success of the program, saying he had given up hope of being a star.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/entertainment/television/tom-gleeson-says-he-had-given-up-hope-of-tv-stardom-before-the-shock-success-of-hard-quiz/news-story/8a8b33a3109f060c262d1d3766f78d8f|title=How Tom Gleeson became a star|last=|first=|date=|work=The Courier-Mail|access-date=2017-05-23|publisher=News Corp|url-access=subscription |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 May 2019, Gleeson announced he was stepping down as host and quitting the program via a media release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/nonstoptom/status/1131786904221786112?s=21|title=I\u2019ve quit #HardQuiz.pic.twitter.com/sZwNYpyyPC|last=Gleeson|first=Tom|date=2019-05-23|website=@nonstoptom|language=en|access-date=2019-05-24}}</ref> On 26 May 2019, Gleeson was announced as a nominee for the [[Gold Logie Award for Most Popular Personality on Australian Television]]. He later tweeted that he would \"un-axe\" the show if he wins the Gold Logie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/nonstoptom/status/1132513834130788353|title=I\u2019M UP FOR THE GOLD LOGIE!|last=Gleeson|first=Tom|date=2019-05-26|website=@nonstoptom|language=en|access-date=2019-05-26}}</ref> Gleeson subsequently won the Gold Logie, and show was announced to be returning on 31 July 2019.\n\nIt was announced by Gleeson on 31 July 2019, in a radio interview with [[Triple M (radio network)|Triple M]], that the show's return in 2020 for its fifth series would see it expand to 40 new episodes.<ref name=\"TVBlackbox\">{{cite web|first=Kevin|last=Perry|title=Gold Logie winning TOM GLEESON to go even HARDER with double HARD QUIZ in 2020|url=https://tvblackbox.com.au/page/2019/8/1/tom-gleeson-to-go-even-harder-in-2020?format=non-amp|website=TV Blackbox|date=2 August 2019|accessdate=2 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Format==\n''Hard Quiz'' features four contestants, each of which have selected a specialist subject area. The contestants in turn each receive 5 questions regarding their specialist subject areas (\"The Experts' Round\"), followed by questions from a subject Gleeson chooses (\"Tom's Round\") and then [[general knowledge]] questions (\"The People's Round\"). Contestants receive 5 points for answering a question correctly, and lose 5 points for answering a question incorrectly.  During the Experts' Round, a contestant may attempt to answer a question from another contestant's subject area. This is known as \"The Steal\". If a Steal is successful, the contestant receives 10 points but will only lose 5 points for an incorrect Steal attempt (in series 1, a failed Steal resulted in the contestant losing 10 points).  The contestant with the lowest score at the end of both the Experts Round and The People's Round are eliminated from the show. In the event of a tie for lowest scorer, the tie is broken with a Hard-Off, where Gleeson presents two options for a given question (often pertaining to the relative difficulty of two given tasks or physical hardness of two materials), which the first contestant to buzz in then answers. If the answering contestant chooses correctly, the other contestant is eliminated and vice versa if the answer given is incorrect. The final two contestants answer questions regarding their chosen subject area in a best of 5 [[penalty shootout]]-style format, with the winner receiving a trophy \u2013 the Hard Quiz Big Brass Mug.\n\n==Series Overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color1     = skyblue\n| link1      = <includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#Series 1 (2016)\n| episodes1  = 10\n| start1     = {{Start date|2016|10|19|df=y}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2016|12|21|df=y}}\n\n| color2     = orange\n| link2      = <includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#Series 2 (2017)\n| episodes2  = 18\n| start2     = {{Start date|2017|8|2|df=y}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2017|11|29|df=y}}\n\n| color3     = #C8A2C8\n| link3      = <includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#Series 3 (2018-19)\n| episodes3  = 22\n| start3     = {{Start date|2018|2|21|df=y}}\n| end3       = {{End date|2019|1|30|df=y}}\n\n| color4     = #FBCEB1\n| link4      = <includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#Series 4 (2019)\n| episodes4  = 20 + [[<includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#ep71|1 Special]]\n| start4     = {{Start date|2019|2|6|df=y}}\n| end4       = {{End date|2019|10|2|df=y}}\n\n| color5     = #9D296E\n| link5      = <includeonly>Hard Quiz</includeonly>#Series 5 (2020)\n| episodes5  = 40<ref name=\"TVBlackbox\" />\n| start5     = {{Start date|2020|2|5|df=y}}\n| end5       = \n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n\n===Series 1 (2016)===\n\n''Names in '''Bold''' are the winners''\n{{Episode table |total_width=70 |background=skyblue |overall=5 |title=16 |viewers=16 |airdate=16 |viewersT=Australian viewers |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| RTitle          = \"Episode 1\"\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|19|df=y}}\n| Viewers         = 681,000<ref>{{cite web|first=David|last=Knox|title=Timeshifted: Wednesday 19 October 2016|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/10/timeshifted-wednesday-19-october-2016.html|website=TV Tonight|date=29 October 2016|accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Quizzers:<br>Sue - [[National flag|Flags]] Expert<br>Liz - [[Brat Pack (actors)|Brat Pack]] Expert<br>Miles - ''[[Doctor Who]]'' Expert<br>'''Mark - [[Field marshal (United Kingdom)|British Army Field Marshals]] Expert'''\n\nTom's Round: Tom's Subject - [[Burke and Wills expedition|Burke & Wills]]\n| LineColor       = skyblue\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| RTitle          = \"Episode 2\"\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|26|df=y}}\n| Viewers         = 532,000<ref>{{cite web|first=David|last=Knox|title=Timeshifted: Wednesday 26 October 2016|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/11/timeshifted-wednesday-26-october-2016.html|website=TV Tonight|date=6 November 2016|accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Quizzers:<br>Lucy - [[Wars of the Roses]] Expert<br>James - [[Military aviation|Military Aviation]] Expert<br>Pierre - [[Punk Rock]] Expert<br>'''Renae - [[Richard Gasquet]] Expert'''\n\nTom's Round: Tom's Subject - [[Greek alphabet|Greek Alphabet]]\n\nNote: This episode features the first ever \"Hard-Off\" and the first ever 3-Way \"Hard-Off\".\n| LineColor       = skyblue\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\