ory:2017 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2018 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2019 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:Split television seasons]]\n[[Category:American Dad! (season 15) episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Season of television series}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| season_number = 15\n| bgcolour      = #2FCE1F\n| image         =\n| image_alt     = \n| caption       = \n| country       = United States\n| num_episodes  = 22\n| network       = [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]]\n| first_aired   = {{Start date|2017|12|25}}\n| last_aired    = {{End date|2019|4|8}}\n| episode_list  = List of American Dad! episodes\n}}\n''[[American Dad!]]''{{'s}} fifteenth season began with a [[Christmas]] special, which aired on December 25, 2017<ref>{{cite press release |title=TBS Schedules \"American Dad!\" Christmas Special for Monday, December 25 |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2017/12/07/tbs-schedules-american-dad-christmas-special-for-monday-december-25-15212/20171207tbs01/ |publisher=Turner Broadcasting System, Inc.  |date=2018-12-07 |access-date=2018-03-05}}</ref> on [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]]. The season would officially premiere on February 12, 2018, and conclude on April 8, 2019.<ref>{{cite press release |date=2018-01-11 |title=TBS Announces New Monday Night Animation Block with Season Premiere of \"American Dad!\" and Series Premiere of \"Final Space\" |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/01/11/tbs-announces-new-monday-night-animation-block-with-season-premiere-of-american-dad-and-series-premiere-of-final-space-708511/20180111tbs02/ |publisher=Turner Broadcasting System, Inc.  |access-date=2018-03-05}}</ref> The series went on hiatus after the season's thirteenth episode aired May 7, 2018. The remaining 9 episodes of the season would begin airing on February 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/american-dad/276801/american-dad-to-air-31-episodes-in-2019|title=American Dad To Air 31 Episodes in 2019|first1=Daniel|last1=Kurland|date=October 7, 2018|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=October 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{see also|List of American Dad! episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table |background=#2FCE1F |overall=5 |season=5 |title=25 |director=17 |writer=20 |airdate=12 |prodcode=7 |viewers=9 |country=US |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|American Dad! (season 15)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 235\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = Santa, Schmanta\n| DirectedBy      = Joe Daniello\n| WrittenBy       = [[Teresa Hsiao]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|12|25}}\n| ProdCode        = CAJN08\n| Viewers         = 0.86<ref>{{cite web|last=Welch |first=Alex |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-cable-ratings-dec-25-2017/ |title=Monday cable ratings: NBA and NFL dominate, \u2018Doctor Who\u2019 Christmas special holds steady |publisher=Tvbythenumbers |date=2017-12-27 |accessdate=2018-02-13}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = In this loose sequel to \"Ninety North, Zero West,\" Roger (upset that no one in the family will pay attention to him) befriends Snot (who's upset over not celebrating Christmas because of his religion) and converts to Judaism, then finds the corpse of Santa Claus and becomes Schmanta, a Santa Claus with the power to make Hanukkah more popular than Christmas.\n| LineColor       = 2FCE1F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|American Dad! (season 15)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 236\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Paranoid Frandroid\n| DirectedBy      = Pam Cooke & Valerie Fletcher\n| WrittenBy       = Joel Hurwitz\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|2|12}}\n| ProdCode        = CAJN01\n| Viewers         = 0.78<ref>{{cite web|last=Welch |first=Alex |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-cable-ratings-feb-12-2018/ |title=Monday cable ratings: \u2018WWE Raw\u2019 holds steady |publisher=Tvbythenumbers |date=2018-02-13 |accessdate=2018-02-23}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Francine becomes hooked on conspiracy theories after discovering that her favorite morning show, ''Morning Mimosa'', is an elaborate CIA ploy conducted by Stan to keep her docile and ignorant of the real world. Meanwhile, Steve and Klaus help Snot and his mom move into an upper-class neighborhood after Snot's mom's boyfriend invites them over, but things get complicated when Snot's mother falls for Klaus.\n| LineColor       = 2FCE1F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|American Dad! (season 15)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 237\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = The Census of the Lambs\n| DirectedBy      = Tim Parsons & Jennifer Graves\n| WrittenBy       = Sam Brenner\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|2|19}}\n| ProdCode        = CAJN02\n| Viewers         = 0.83<ref>{{cite web|last=Welch |first=Alex |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-cable-ratings-feb-19-2018/ |title=Monday cable ratings: \u2018The Alienist\u2019 holds steady, \u2018Love & Hip Hop: Miami\u2019 ticks up |publisher=Tvbythenumbers |date=2018-02-21 |accessdate=2018-03-03}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = After Stan is chosen to be an enumerator for the Census, he ends up competing with Hayley over who can count the most residents...and gets abducted by a serial killer. Meanwhile, Klaus becomes a photographer after finding his uncle's old camera and chooses Steve's friend, Barry, to be his star model.\n| LineColor       = 2FCE1F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|American Dad! (season 15)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 238\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Shell Game\n| DirectedBy      = Chris Bennett\n| WrittenBy       = Brett Cawley & Robert Maitia\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|2|26}}\n| ProdCode        = CAJN03\n| Viewers         = 0.73<ref>{{cite web|last=Welch |first=Alex |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-cable-ratings-feb-26-2018/ |title=Monday cable ratings: 'WWE Raw' leads, 'The Alienist' ticks up |publisher=Tvbythenumbers |date=2018-02-27 |accessdate=2018-03-07}}</ref>\n| ShortSumma