{"title_page": "Augmented tree-based routing", "text_new": "'''Augmented tree-based routing (ATR)''' [[Communications protocol|protocol]], first proposed in 2007, is a multi-path [[Distributed hash table|DHT]]-based routing protocol for scalable [[Computer network|network]]s. ATR resorts to an augmented tree-based [[address space]] structure and a hierarchical multi-path routing protocol in order to gain [[scalability]] and good resilience against [[node (networking)|node]] failure/mobility and link congestion/instability.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mobile ad hoc network]]\n* [[Ad hoc routing protocol list]]\n\n==References==\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1109/MOBHOC.2007.4428727 |isbn=978-1-4244-1454-3 |arxiv=0711.3099 |chapter=Augmented Tree-based Routing Protocol for Scalable Ad Hoc Networks |title=2007 IEEE Internatonal Conference on Mobile Adhoc and Sensor Systems |pages=1\u20136 |year=2007 |last1=Caleffi |first1=Marcello |last2=Ferraiuolo |first2=Giancarlo |last3=Paura |first3=Luigi }}\n* {{cite book |arxiv=0801.4082 |bibcode=2008arXiv0801.4082C |chapter=On Reliability of Dynamic Addressing Routing Protocols in Mobile Ad Hoc Networks |last1=Caleffi |first1=Marcello |last2=Ferraiuolo |first2=Giancarlo |last3=Paura |first3=Luigi |year=2008 |title=Proceedings of WRECOM '07: Wireless Rural and Emergency Communications Conference, Roma (Italy), October 2007}}\n\n[[Category:Routing algorithms]]\n[[Category:Wireless networking]]\n[[Category:Ad hoc routing protocols]]\n\n\n{{compu-network-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=March 2011}}\n\n'''Augmented tree-based routing (ATR)''' [[Communications protocol|protocol]], first proposed in 2007, is a multi-path [[Distributed hash table|DHT]]-based routing protocol for scalable [[Computer network|network]]s. ATR resorts to an augmented tree-based [[address space]] structure and a hierarchical multi-path routing protocol in order to gain [[scalability]] and good resilience against [[node (networking)|node]] failure/mobility and link congestion/instability.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mobile ad hoc network]]\n* [[Ad hoc routing protocol list]]\n\n==References==\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1109/MOBHOC.2007.4428727 |isbn=978-1-4244-1454-3 |arxiv=0711.3099 |chapter=Augmented Tree-based Routing Protocol for Scalable Ad Hoc Networks |title=2007 IEEE Internatonal Conference on Mobile Adhoc and Sensor Systems |pages=1\u20136 |year=2007 |last1=Caleffi |first1=Marcello |last2=Ferraiuolo |first2=Giancarlo |last3=Paura |first3=Luigi }}\n* {{cite book |arxiv=0801.4082 |bibcode=2008arXiv0801.4082C |chapter=On Reliability of Dynamic Addressing Routing Protocols in Mobile Ad Hoc Networks |last1=Caleffi |first1=Marcello |last2=Ferraiuolo |first2=Giancarlo |last3=Paura |first3=Luigi |year=2008 |title=Proceedings of WRECOM '07: Wireless Rural and Emergency Communications Conference, Roma (Italy), October 2007}}\n\n[[Category:Routing algorithms]]\n[[Category:Wireless networking]]\n[[Category:Ad hoc routing protocols]]\n\n\n{{compu-network-stub}}\n", "name_user": "FreeToDisagree", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed the orphan-tag since the article is no longer an orphan.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Augmented_tree-based_routing"}
